Source: pg-task
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), systemtap-sdt-dev, wget, pcre2-utils
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/RekGRpth/pg_task

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-task
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-task
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: PostgreSQL job scheduler for asynchronous SQL tasks
  pg_task is a PostgreSQL, Greenplum, and Greengage job scheduler that runs
  SQL commands asynchronously at a specific time in the background.
